article.headline: Campbell 93, North Florida 75
article.story: BUIES CREEK, N.C. (AP) -- Maurice Latham and Eric Smith each scored 25 points as Campbell easily defeated North Florida 93-75 in the Atlantic Sun Conference on Saturday. Ruell Pringle and Ledell Eackles added 14 points apiece for the Fighting Camels (7-12, 6-6), who led by as many as 29 down the stretch. Rashad Williams and Ryan Daugherty each had 17 points for the Ospreys (5-14, 2-10) while Chris Timberlake added 12. Alain Laroche had a game-high 16 rebounds. Campbell led 46-33 at the break and converted 20 North Florida turnovers into 31 points. The Fighting Camels led by double figures for the entire second period. North Florida is now 0-10 on the road this year, 0-7 against A-Sun opponents.
